\end{lem}
The next result determines periodicity and perfect state transfer in cubelike graphs at $t=\frac{\pi}{2}$. For other values of $t$, those properties are not completely characterized in cubelike graphs.
\begin{theorem}\label{2c}\cite{chi}
Let $C$ be a subset of ${\mathbb Z}_{2}^{n}$ and let $\sigma$ be the sum of the elements of $C$. If $\sigma\neq {\mathbf 0}$ then PST occurs in $X(C)$ from $u$ to $u+\sigma$ at time $\frac{\pi}{2}$. If $\sigma={\mathbf 0}$ then $X$ is periodic at $\frac{\pi}{2}$. 
\end{theorem}
